-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 8
-- 
-- Wed Oct 08, 2014 02:17AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 8 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Three senior female members of centre-right GERB party will hold the first round of talks with other political parties on forming a government, the party said. (Monitor, 24 Chasa, Trud, Presa, Sega, Capital Daily) -- Bulgaria has 6 months to choose new jet fighters for the army, the defence ministry said. The country will most likely buy eight second-hand F-16 for about $400 million. (Monitor, Presa) -- The interim government has appointed Dimitar Gogov as head of Bulgarian company involved in South Stream gas pipeline project. (Monitor, 24 Chasa, Presa, Sega, Trud) 24 CHASA - The International Monetary Fund cut its forecast for Bulgaria's economic growth to 1.4 percent from 1.6 percent.